            "text": "The 5-3-2 formation is football’s answer to a brick wall—ideal for frustrating strong opponents and keeping things tight at the back. With five defenders across the rear guard, you’re well equipped to repel wave after wave of attacks. The midfield trio works hard to provide cover, while also keeping an eye out for counterattacking opportunities. The two strikers remain poised to exploit any defensive lapses from the opposition. It’s a setup that says, “Break us down if you can,” and is particularly effective against teams that love to dominate possession. The trade-off? You might be light on numbers going forward, but when defensive solidity is the priority, the 5-3-2 is a tough nut to crack.",
